---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Create Document | Farhan Ahmed">
  <div class="min-h-screen pt-8 pb-32">
    <div class="mb-8 animate-fade-in">
      <a 
        href="/docs" 
        class="inline-flex items-center text-emerald-400 hover:text-emerald-300 text-sm group transition-colors"
      >
        <svg 
          xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" 
          class="h-4 w-4 mr-1 transition-transform group-hover:-translate-x-1" 
          viewBox="0 0 20 20" 
          fill="currentColor"
        >
          <path 
            fill-rule="evenodd" 
            d="M9.707 16.707a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-6-6a1 1 0 010-1.414l6-6a1 1 0 011.414 1.414L5.414 9H17a1 1 0 110 2H5.414l4.293 4.293a1 1 0 010 1.414z" 
            clip-rule="evenodd"
          />
        </svg>
        <span class="relative">
          Back to Documentation
        </span>
      </a>
    </div>
    
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-8 animate-fade-in">Create New Document</h1>
      
      <div 
        class="rounded-lg glass-effect hover-card animate-fade-in"
      >
        <div class="p-6 space-y-6">
          <div>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-medium text-white mb-3">Document Template</h2>
            <p class="text-white/70 mb-4 text-sm">
              To create a new document, you need to create a Markdown file in the <code>src/content/docs</code> directory. 
              Use the following template as a starting point:
            </p>
            
            <div class="bg-black/20 p-4 rounded-md overflow-auto mb-4 border border-white/5">
              <pre class="text-white/80 text-xs"><code>---
title: 'Document Title'
description: 'Brief description of the document'
pubDate: 2025-04-01
updatedDate: 2025-04-05
category: 'Category Name'
order: 1
tags: ['tag1', 'tag2', 'tag3']
---

# Main Heading

Introduction paragraph goes here.

## Sub Heading

Content goes here.

### Smaller Heading

More content here.

- List item 1
- List item 2
- List item 3

```javascript
// Code example
function example() {
  return 'Hello, world!';
}
```

> Blockquote text goes here

[Link text](https://example.com)

![Image alt text](https://example.com/image.jpg)
</code></pre>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-medium text-white mb-3">Front Matter Explanation</h2>
            <div class="overflow-x-auto">
              <table class="w-full text-white/80 text-sm">
                <tr class="border-b border-white/10">
                  <th class="text-left py-2 px-3 text-emerald-400 font-medium">Field</th>
                  <th class="text-left py-2 px-3 text-emerald-400 font-medium">Description</th>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-b border-white/5 hover:bg-white/5">
                  <td class="py-2 px-3 font-medium">title</td>
                  <td class="py-2 px-3">The title of your document</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-b border-white/5 hover:bg-white/5">
                  <td class="py-2 px-3 font-medium">description</td>
                  <td class="py-2 px-3">A brief description that appears in the document listing</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-b border-white/5 hover:bg-white/5">
                  <td class="py-2 px-3 font-medium">pubDate</td>
                  <td class="py-2 px-3">Publication date in YYYY-MM-DD format</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-b border-white/5 hover:bg-white/5">
                  <td class="py-2 px-3 font-medium">updatedDate</td>
                  <td class="py-2 px-3">Optional. Date when the document was last updated</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-b border-white/5 hover:bg-white/5">
                  <td class="py-2 px-3 font-medium">category</td>
                  <td class="py-2 px-3">The category the document belongs to (e.g., "AWS", "Java", "React")</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-b border-white/5 hover:bg-white/5">
                  <td class="py-2 px-3 font-medium">order</td>
                  <td class="py-2 px-3">Numerical order within the category (lower numbers appear first)</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-b border-white/5 hover:bg-white/5">
                  <td class="py-2 px-3 font-medium">tags</td>
                  <td class="py-2 px-3">Array of tags related to the document</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="hover:bg-white/5">
                  <td class="py-2 px-3 font-medium">heroImage</td>
                  <td class="py-2 px-3">Optional. URL to a hero image for the document</td>
                </tr>
              </table>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-medium text-white mb-3">Special Styling</h2>
            <p class="text-white/70 mb-3 text-sm">
              You can use these special classes to highlight important information:
            </p>
            
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-3">
              <div class="p-3 rounded-md bg-blue-500/5 border-l-2 border-blue-400">
                <h3 class="font-medium text-blue-400 text-sm mb-1">Note</h3>
                <code class="text-xs text-white/70">{`<div class="note">This is a note</div>`}</code>
              </div>
              
              <div class="p-3 rounded-md bg-amber-500/5 border-l-2 border-amber-400">
                <h3 class="font-medium text-amber-400 text-sm mb-1">Warning</h3>
                <code class="text-xs text-white/70">{`<div class="warning">This is a warning</div>`}</code>
              </div>
              
              <div class="p-3 rounded-md bg-emerald-500/5 border-l-2 border-emerald-400">
                <h3 class="font-medium text-emerald-400 text-sm mb-1">Tip</h3>
                <code class="text-xs text-white/70">{`<div class="tip">This is a tip</div>`}</code>
              </div>
              
              <div class="p-3 rounded-md bg-red-500/5 border-l-2 border-red-400">
                <h3 class="font-medium text-red-400 text-sm mb-1">Danger</h3>
                <code class="text-xs text-white/70">{`<div class="danger">This is a danger notice</div>`}</code>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-medium text-white mb-3">File Naming</h2>
            <p class="text-white/70 text-sm">
              Name your file with a descriptive slug, using kebab-case:
              <code class="px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-xs bg-white/5 text-emerald-300">src/content/docs/aws-lambda-functions.md</code>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="mt-8 text-center">
        <a 
          href="/docs" 
          class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-emerald-600 text-white text-sm rounded-md hover:bg-emerald-700 transition-all duration-300"
        >
          Return to Documentation
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>